{{short description|Australian philosopher}} {{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Dirk Baltzly''' |birth_date = 1963 |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Ancient philosophy]] | institutions = [[University of Tasmania]] |main_interests = [[virtue ethics]] | thesis_title = Plato's Argument From Relatives: The Role of the Distinction Between Kath Hauto and Pros Ti in the Theory of Forms | thesis_url = https://etd.ohiolink.edu/!etd.send_file?accession=osu1487777901657771&disposition=inline | thesis_year = 1992 | doctoral_advisor = [[Allan Silverman]] | doctoral_students = |notable_ideas = | spouse = | education = [[Ohio State University]] (PhD), [[Monash University]] (PhD) | alma_mater = |influences = [[Pre-Socratics]], [[Plato]], [[Aristotle]], [[Epicureans]] |awards = |website = http://www.utas.edu.au/profiles/staff/humanities/dirk-baltzly }}
'''Dirk Christian Baltzly''' (born 1963) is an Australian philosopher and Professor of [[Philosophy]] at the [[University of Tasmania]]. He is known for his research on [[ancient Greek and Roman Philosophy]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Karamanolis |first1=George |title=Ancient Interpretations of Plato - (H.) Tarrant, (D.) Baltzly (edd.) Reading Plato in Antiquity. Pp. x + 268, figs. London: Duckworth, 2006. Cased, £50. |isbn=0-7156-3455-0 |journal=[[The Classical Review]] |date=April 2009 |volume=59 |issue=1 |pages=56–58 |doi=10.1017/S0009840X08001820 |url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/classical-review/article/div-classtitleancient-interprertations-of-plato-tarranth-baltzlyd-edd-reading-plato-in-antiquity-pp-x-268-figs-london-duckworth-2006-cased-50-isbn-0-7156-3455-0div/5F5A5716893623D991C046EB963D882F |accessdate=24 October 2018 |language=en |issn=1464-3561}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Fletcher |first1=Richard |title=Philosophy - (H.) Tarrant and (D.) Baltzly Reading Plato in Antiquity. London: Duckworth, 2006. Pp. ix + 268. £50. 9780715634554. |journal=The Journal of Hellenic Studies |date=November 2008 |volume=128 |pages=282–282 |doi=10.1017/S0075426900001294 |url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/journal-of-hellenic-studies/article/div-classtitlephilosophy-tarranth-and-baltzlydreading-plato-in-antiquity-london-duckworth-2006-pp-ix-268-50-9780715634554div/C18B7FB87BF21EFF7193C4FA9F3AE181 |accessdate=24 October 2018 |language=en |issn=2041-4099}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=O'Daly |first1=Gerard J. P. |title=Proclus' Commentary on Plato's Republic |journal=[[The Classical Review]] |date=1983 |volume=33 |issue=2 |pages=242–244 |url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/3063964?seq=1#page_scan_tab_contents |accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref> Baltzly is a Fellow of the [[Australian Academy of Humanities]] (2008).<ref>{{cite web |title=Dirk Baltzly |url=http://www.utas.edu.au/profiles/staff/humanities/dirk-baltzly |website=Profiles - University of Tasmania, Australia |accessdate=24 October 2018 |language=en-AU |date=21 August 2013}}</ref>
