{{Infobox company | name = GLS Bank | logo = GLS Logo RGB 800px.jpg | logo_size = 200px | type = [[Cooperative]] | foundation = 1974 | location = [[Bochum]], [[Germany]] | key_people = [[Thomas Jorberg]], President | products = [[Sustainable banking]] | homepage = [https://www.gls.de/ www.gls.de] | industry = [[Financial services]] | num_employees = 514 (2017) | revenue = | net_income = | aum = [[Euro|€]] 4.1 [[1000000000 (number)|billion]] (2016) }}
'''GLS Bank''' (full name '''GLS Gemeinschaftsbank eG''') is a German [[ethical banking|ethical bank]] that was founded in 1974 as an [[anthroposophy|anthroposophical]] initiative by [[Wilhelm Ernst Barkhoff]] and Gisela Reuther. It was the first bank in Germany that operated with an [[Ethical banking|ethical philosophy]].<ref name=inaise>''GLS Gemeinschaftsbank'', summary by International Association of Investors in the Social Economy, December 2006. [http://www.inaise.org For summary report enter 'GLS' in search box]</ref> According to GLS Bank, its focus is on cultural, social and ecological initiatives, initiated by people, and not anonymous interests seeking capital or maximum profit. The name stands for ''Gemeinschaftsbank für Leihen und Schenken'' which translates as ''Community bank for loaning and giving''. With the main focus on cultural, social and environmental ventures, GLS tries to deal with challenges in the society by developing creative solutions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gls.de/die-gls-bank/ueber-uns/gls-bank/english-portrait.html |title=GLS Bank: A brief portrait - GLS Bank |work=gls.de |year=2011 |accessdate=31 March 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719033149/http://www.gls.de/die-gls-bank/ueber-uns/gls-bank/english-portrait.html |archivedate=19 July 2011 |df= }}</ref>
[[File:GLS Bank.jpg|thumb|left| The head office of the German GLS Bank in [[Bochum]], [[Germany]]]] The bank is based in [[Bochum]], Germany and is a [[co-operative]]. As of November 2006, the bank's total balance was EUR 645 million.<ref name=inaise/> As of 31 December 2008, the balance sheet total was EUR 1,013 million, further rising to EUR 1,847 million as of 31 December 2010.
In 2015, the bank received the first ''German Award for Excellence'' from the [[DQS|Deutschen Gesellschaft für Zertifizierung ''(German Certification Group)'']].<ref>[https://umwelt-kompass.com/kompass/gls-bank-fuer-vorbildliche-geschaeftspolitik-ausgezeichnet/#more-251123 GLS Bank für vorbildliche Geschäftspolitik ausgezeichnet], Umwelt-Kompass</ref><ref>[http://www.nna-news.org/de/nachrichten/artikel/erstmals-verliehener-german-award-for-excellence-geht-an-gls-bank-2494/ Erstmals verliehener „German Award for Excellence“ geht an GLS-Bank]</ref> The award was granted to honor the bank's fair business practices.
In December 2016 at the annual general assembly, about 80% of the 1200 people present at the assembly decided to introduce the ''GLS Beitrag''.<ref>[https://blog.gls.de/gls-gemeinschaft/gls-beitrag-im-neuland/ GLS Beitrag: Im Neuland], GLS Blog</ref><ref>[http://bankspiegel.pageflow.io/gls-beitrag bankspiegel.pageflow.io/gls-beitrag], pageflow.io</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.handelsblatt.com/finanzen/banken-versicherungen/gls-bank-gebuehr-ohne-schrecken/19333032.html |title=Gebühr ohne Schrecken |work=Handelsblatt |year=2017 |accessdate=25 September 2017 }}</ref>
==Growth== In 2010, the bank acquired over 18,000 new customers and in February 2011 GLS announced a growth of 37 per cent, the largest in the bank's history.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nna-news.org/news/en/index.cgi/110215-01EN_GLS-RECORD-GROWTH.html |title=GLS Bank with 37 percent record growth |work=nna-news.org |year=2011 |accessdate=14 July 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111006063933/http://www.nna-news.org/news/en/index.cgi/110215-01EN_GLS-RECORD-GROWTH.html |archivedate=6 October 2011 |df= }}</ref> As of December 2016 the Genossenschaft (co-operative) has 46.313 members,<ref name="GLS Bank">[https://www.gls.de/privatkunden/gls-bank/zahlen-fakten/ GLS Bank], Zahlen & Fakten</ref> compared to December 2015 with 41.982 members<ref name="GLS Bank"/> this is a growth of 10.3%.<ref name="GLS Bank"/>
