{{Chinese folk religion}}
The '''Taigu school''' (太谷学派 ''Tàigǔ xuépài''), also '''Great Perfection''' (大成教 ''Dàchéng jiào'') or '''Yellow Cliff teaching''' (黄崖教 ''Huángyá jiào''), is a [[mystical]] [[Chinese folk religion|folk religious]] sect of [[Confucianism]] spread especially in [[Jiangsu]], [[Anhui]] and [[Shandong]]. It was founded by Zhou Xingyuan, a man with [[shamanic]] skills entitled ''Taigu'' (太谷 "Great Valley") by followers.{{sfnb|Ma|2007|p=239}}

The purpose of the school is to help those who practice it to develop a clear and enlightened state of mind, in which man apprehends his true nature and recovers original simplicity.{{sfnb|Ma|2007|p=233}}

